      "writtenOn": "2026-07-16T02:41:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The generic SPIFlash type is too broad because a system can have multiple different SPI devices that require different update or version get behaviors.\n\nBy adopting a \u003cVendor\u003e\u003cChip/Device\u003e naming pattern—similar to how CPLDs are currently handled in EM—we improve scalability and maintainability. This ensures the backend can easily differentiate and scale for future SPI devices.",
      "parentUuid": "8bc869c8_bce7266d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 8,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 11,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "dd911ce80ef54d990d4b126f689e8780e46bd126",
