      "writtenOn": "2026-07-15T12:06:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The current behavior when using Type `SPIFlash` is complete chip overwrite without special handling of any flash regions or headers.\n\nWhen using your new `IntelHostSPIFlash` type, will it be the same behavior?\n\nIn that case, what does it have to do with intel?\n\n\n\nThe flash layout (and descriptors) are separate (with some overlap) from flash partitions.\n\nThose 2 concepts are themselves still separate from the purpose of the contents.\n\nIn the end result we have 3 concepts all of which can probably be configured as separate properties.\n\n- flash descriptors (intel with IFD or none (generic)). That was covered by `{IntelSPIFlash, SPIFlash}`\n- flash partitions (my pending PR)\n- purpose (BIOS fw, BMC fw, CPLD fw, VR fw, ... whatever)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 84,
        "startChar": 47,
        "endLine": 84,
        "endChar": 64
      },
      "revId": "dd911ce80ef54d990d4b126f689e8780e46bd126",
