      "writtenOn": "2026-07-16T02:41:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "To clarify the behavior: `IntelHostSPIFlash` does not do a simple full chip overwrite. It maps to `flashrom` in the backend, which handles the Intel Flash Descriptor and specific regions. The generic `HostSPIFlash` maps to `flashcp`. Therefore, the \"Intel\" prefix is functionally required right now to select the correct backend tool.\n\nFurthermore, adopting the `\u003cVendor\u003e\u003cChip/Device\u003e` pattern accommodates more than just the flashing method. A major difference also lies in the reading mechanisms. The backend needs to cleanly differentiate how to read the version from a Host BIOS versus how to interact with a peripheral device.",
      "parentUuid": "47935f7e_4a3ac548",
